question:
What will be the output of the following code?

```python
class A:
    def __init__(self, x):
        self.x = x

class B(A):
    def __init__(self, x, y):
        super().__init__(x)
        self.y = y

b = B(1, 2)
print(b.x, b.y)
```

What will be the output of the following code?

```python
class A:
    def __init__(self):
        self.x = 1
    def update(self, x):
        self.x += x
class B(A):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.x = 2
b = B()
b.update(3)
print(b.x)
```
